channel.title: Sadly Need Help w/ Port Forwarding
channel.description:
Well Ive taken the tuts, ive done everything you could ever need to do for portforwarding .. I got the submask, ip, all the stuff .. now I have no idea what to do. Heres my problem.
I go to the default site that I [i]have[/i] to use. the site I have to use is 192.168.1.1 and when I go there I type in "admin" as user name and it keeps opening 3 times so I typed the same thing in the three boxes.
Then it went to this one site were it says "404 Authorization Required" So I said "Eh, Must've typed the pass and name in wrong" So then I used admin as the pass. Still, The 404 Authorization Required page came up.
So, I used admin as the username and pass and still, the three boxes still came up. And of course, it went to the 404 Authorization Page. I then asked my parents if they had anything to do with the username and password. They had no idea, so then I tried searching my computor, and my router for the username and pass. I couldn't find anything.
Does anyone know where I can find the username and password? If it helps at all I have Linksys and my module type is WRT54G.
Thanks for reading,
- Boring

item.title: Sadly Need Help w/ Port Forwarding
item.dc:creator: @crakaman crakaman
item.description:
@crakaman wrote:

go to portforward.com and click port forwarding on the upper left a little you will see than under that list find your router than under the next page go down the the Z’s i believe and click zbattle.net and follow the steps in there it should work

Read full topic
